==English==

===Etymology===
From the Greek [[ἀπό]] ("away, apart"), [[στάσις]] ("standing").

Also derived from Greek [[αποστάτης]], meaning "political rebel", as applied to rebellion against God, its law and the faith of Israel (in Hebrew [[מרד]]) in the old testament.

===Pronunciation===
a*pos"ta*sy

===Noun===
'''apostasy'''
#Departure (spatial removal)
#The renunciation of one's [[religion]] or [[faith]].
#The renunciation of a [[belief]] or set of beliefs

